==English==

===Etymology===
{{PIE root|en|(s)pend}}
From {{inh|en|enm|spenden}}, from {{inh|en|ang|spendan}} (attested especially in compounds {{m|ang|āspendan||to spend}}, {{m|ang|forspendan||to use up, consume}}), from late {{inh|en|gem-pro|*spendaną}}, {{m|gem-pro|*spendōną||to spend}}, borrowed from {{der|en|la|expendere||to weigh out}}. {{doublet|en|expend}}. Cognate with {{cog|goh|spentōn||to consume, use, spend}} (whence {{cog|de|spenden||to donate, provide}}), {{etyl|dum|-}} {{m|nl|spenden||to spend, dedicate}}, Old {{cog|is|spenna||to spend}}.

